claim.claim-text:
An inspecting device (100) for inspecting a photo device (90) comprising:
an irradiation part (12) for irradiating said photo device (90) with pulsed light (LP11);
a detection part (13) having a detector (132) for detecting an electric field intensity of an electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) depending on irradiation with probe light (LP12) emitted from a light source (121) for said pulsed light;
a delay part (131) for changing a time difference between a time that said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) arrives at said detector (132) and a time that said probe light (LP12) arrives at said detector (132); thereby delaying a timing for detecting said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) through said detector (132);
a temporal waveform restoration part (21) for restoring a temporal waveform (41, 43) of said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) based on said electric field intensity of said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) detected by said detector (132) in said plurality of pieces of detection timing; and
an electromagnetic wave pulse analysis part (23) for detecting a negative peak of said electric field intensity in said temporal waveform (41, 43).

A method of inspecting a photo device (90) comprising the steps of:
(a) irradiating said photo device (90) with pulsed light;
(b) detecting, through a detector (132), an electric field intensity of an electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) to be radiated from said photo device (90) in said step (a) depending on irradiation with probe light (LP12) emitted from a light source for said pulsed light;
(c) changing a time difference between a time that said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) arrives at said detector (132) and a time that said probe light (LP12) arrives at said detector (132), thereby delaying a timing for detecting said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) through said detector (132) in said step (b);
(d) restoring a temporal waveform (41, 43) of said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) based on said electric field intensity of said electromagnetic wave pulse (LT1) detected in said plurality of pieces of detection timing in said step (b); and
(e) detecting a negative peak of said electric field intensity in said temporal waveform (41, 43) restored in said step (d).
